value.0: This is a Mortarch of Kelemvor. He is a priest whose specialization lays in the arts of funerals. His main duties are to consecrate graves, maintain and pass on knowledge regarding burial customs, and to provide comfort the grieving family members of the deceased. He wears a somber smokey gray vestment, and is currently without his sword. He wears a silver headband which is rarely removed, as well as the symbol of Kelmvor prominetsly displayed. This one has a twinkle in his eye, and while he takes his duties seriously, he is known to make the odd pun now and again.

Value.value: Death is a solemn undertaking. *a wry smile*
We are now under way. *gestures around the shrine*
You don't like my sense of humor?  I have been told it will be the death of me.
Death is but part of life: fear it not, evade it not, and view it not as evil. To fear death delivers you into the hands of those who can bring death down upon you.

Die with dignity, neither raging nor seeking to embrace undeath. Do honor to the dead, for their strivings in life brought Faerun to where it is now, and to forget them is to forget also where we are now - and why.
